# IBM Cloud Simple COS Module

A Terraform module to create a Cloud Object Storage instance with a bucket on IBM Cloud.

## Usage

```hcl
module "simple_cos" {
  source = "github.com/your-org/terraform-ibm-simple-cos"

  ibmcloud_api_key    = var.ibmcloud_api_key
  region              = "us-south"
  resource_group_name = "my-resource-group"
  cos_instance_name   = "my-cos-instance"
  cos_plan            = "standard"
  tags                = ["terraform", "production"]
}
```

## Requirements

| Name | Version |
|------|---------|
| terraform | >= 1.9.0 |
| ibm | >= 1.80.0, < 2.0.0 |

## Inputs

| Name | Description | Type | Default | Required |
|------|-------------|------|---------|:--------:|
| ibmcloud_api_key | IBM Cloud API key | `string` | n/a | yes |
| region | IBM Cloud region | `string` | `"us-south"` | no |
| resource_group_name | Name of the resource group | `string` | n/a | yes |
| cos_instance_name | Name of the COS instance | `string` | n/a | yes |
| cos_plan | Service plan for COS | `string` | `"standard"` | no |
| tags | List of tags | `list(string)` | `[]` | no |

## Outputs

| Name | Description |
|------|-------------|
| resource_group_id | ID of the resource group |
| cos_instance_crn | CRN of the COS instance |
| cos_bucket_name | Name of the COS bucket |
